    24	<!-- ANCHOR:summary -->
    25	## 1. SUMMARY
    26	
    27	### Technical Context
    28	
    29	| Aspect | Value |
    30	|--------|-------|
    31	| **Language/Stack** | Python 3 initializer, Markdown templates, pytest contract tests |
    32	| **Active generator** | `create-skill/scripts/init_skill.py` parent path |
    33	| **Generated contract** | Parent hub `SKILL.md` plus registry/router/description/graph metadata and primary packet |
    34	| **Compiled dependency** | Canonical P3 minter, manifest store, freshness predicate, and data-driven runtime discovery |
    35	| **Compatibility posture** | Existing CLI calls default to legacy; agent workflow asks explicitly |
    36	
    37	### Overview
    38	
    39	The smallest viable change keeps the current generator structure and adds one parent-only state option. Both generated parent templates always receive the additive compiled-routing directive. The state option controls only the manifest lifecycle: `legacy` emits none, while `ready` calls and verifies the canonical P3 minter after router inputs are final.
    40	
    41	The implementation must not build a second compiler or freshness rule inside create-skill. It consumes the stable shared interfaces, updates the active and copy-from templates together, and expands the existing create-skill contract tests.
    42	<!-- /ANCHOR:summary -->
    43	
    44	---
    45	
    46	<!-- ANCHOR:quality-gates -->
    47	## 2. QUALITY GATES
    48	
    49	### Definition of Ready
    50	
    51	- [ ] P3 exposes a stable minter, manifest-location abstraction, freshness predicate, and new-hub runtime discovery.
    52	- [ ] The exact directive block in `spec.md` is approved.
    53	- [ ] Legacy remains the backward-compatible CLI default.
    54	- [ ] Existing create-skill tests pass before implementation changes.
    55	
    56	### Definition of Done
    57	
    58	- [ ] Active and canonical parent templates render matching directive blocks.
    59	- [ ] Legacy and compiled-ready states are explicit and tested.
    60	- [ ] Ready state is reported only after shared freshness verification.
    61	- [ ] Standalone scaffolding and existing parent CLI calls remain compatible.
    62	- [ ] create-skill validation and docs agree with generated behavior.
    63	- [ ] No runtime router, manifest of an existing hub, or frozen scorer file is modified.
    64	<!-- /ANCHOR:quality-gates -->
    65	
    66	---
    67	
    68	<!-- ANCHOR:architecture -->
    69	## 3. ARCHITECTURE
    70	
    71	### Pattern
    72	
    73	Template-plus-postcondition. Rendering establishes the hub's durable routing instruction; the selected onboarding mode establishes whether a valid manifest exists. The shared P3 predicate, not create-skill, decides whether the resulting hub is compiled-eligible.
    74	
    75	### Key Components
    76	
    77	- **CLI/state parser**: accepts `legacy|ready` for parent generation and rejects the option for standalone generation.
    78	- **Directive renderer**: substitutes the hub name into the canonical block in both parent templates.
    79	- **Manifest adapter**: invokes the shared minter and verifies the returned canonical manifest for ready mode.
    80	- **State reporter**: emits one of two unambiguous results and never treats fallback as ready.
    81	- **Contract tests**: create temp hubs and inspect emitted files plus minter/freshness outcomes.
    82	
    83	### Data Flow
    84	
    85	```text
    86	create-skill request
    87	      |
    88	      v
    89	standalone? ---- yes ----> existing standalone path unchanged
    90	      |
    91	      v parent
    92	choose legacy|ready
    93	      |
    94	      v
    95	render hub + exact directive
    96	      |
    97	      +---- legacy ----> no manifest ----> report legacy
    98	      |
    99	      +---- ready -----> canonical minter -> freshness predicate
   100	                                             | pass -> report compiled-ready
   101	                                             | fail -> non-zero, no ready claim
   102	```
   103	<!-- /ANCHOR:architecture -->
   104	
