   193	## L2: PHASE DEPENDENCIES
   194	
   195	```text
   196	P0 front door/status + P3 eligibility
   197	                 |
   198	                 v
   199	baseline -> parity module -> orchestrator/report -> fixtures/tests -> adoption
   200	```
   201	
   202	| Phase | Depends On | Blocks |
   203	|-------|------------|--------|
   204	| Setup | Stable P0/P3 interfaces | Core implementation |
   205	| Core implementation | Setup | Verification |
   206	| Verification | Core implementation | Lane C compiled-reality gate |
   207	<!-- /ANCHOR:phase-deps -->
   208	
   209	---
   210	
   211	<!-- ANCHOR:effort -->
   212	## L2: EFFORT ESTIMATION
   213	
   214	| Phase | Complexity | Relative Effort |
   215	|-------|------------|-----------------|
   216	| Interface and baseline capture | Medium | Cross-packet contract inspection |
   217	| Parity module | High | Multi-shape normalization and status handling |
   218	| Orchestrator/report integration | Medium | Additive gate with score non-regression |
   219	| Fixtures and tests | High | Full state and bundle matrix |
   220	| Documentation | Low | README, CLI, report schema |
   221	<!-- /ANCHOR:effort -->
   222	
   223	---
   224	
   225	<!-- ANCHOR:enhanced-rollback -->
   226	## L2: ENHANCED ROLLBACK
   227	
   228	### Pre-Implementation Checklist
   229	
   230	- [ ] Frozen file hashes captured.
   231	- [ ] Representative legacy reports captured.
   232	- [ ] All fixtures are temp/injected and cannot reach production manifests.
   233	- [ ] Parent environment snapshot is asserted in tests.
   234	
   235	### Rollback Procedure
   236	
   237	1. Disable/remove the new parity call from the orchestrator.
   238	2. Restore prior report rendering and usage text.
   239	3. Run the existing Lane C suite and compare representative reports to baseline.
   240	4. Re-hash the frozen files and halt if any digest differs.
   241	
   242	### Data Reversal
   243	
   244	- **Has persistent data changes?** No.
   245	- **Reversal procedure**: Delete only test-temp output through the test harness; production manifests and routing inputs are never mutated by design.
   246	<!-- /ANCHOR:enhanced-rollback -->
