.opencode/skills/system-code-graph/manual-testing-playbook/plugins-and-hooks/code-graph-freshness-guard.md:26:`mk-code-graph-freshness` lets an already-established, warm structural code graph self-heal from soft-stale back to fresh without an operator manually re-running a scan. After a source-file Write/Edit lands, it debounces the edit burst per session, and -- only when the graph is not empty and the daemon is already warm -- fire-and-forget dispatches a warm-only incremental `code_graph_scan`. It never blocks the tool call it observed, never cold-starts the daemon, and never writes stdout/stderr.
.opencode/skills/system-code-graph/manual-testing-playbook/plugins-and-hooks/code-graph-freshness-guard.md:51:  - A `scan` decision carries `dispatch.bin = ".opencode/bin/code-index.cjs"` with args including `code_graph_scan`, `--json` `{"incremental":true}`, and `--warm-only`.
.opencode/skills/system-code-graph/manual-testing-playbook/plugins-and-hooks/code-graph-freshness-guard.md:54:  - The shared scan lock (`.scan.lock`) never survives past the dispatching process's own exit.
.opencode/skills/system-code-graph/manual-testing-playbook/plugins-and-hooks/code-graph-freshness-guard.md:78:3. Exercise `evaluateEdit()`/`classifyEditScope()`/`probeDaemonWarm()` directly against real, hermetic temp-project fixtures (in-scope filter, cold-daemon debounce, scan dispatch, empty-graph gate, kill-switch):
.opencode/skills/system-code-graph/manual-testing-playbook/plugins-and-hooks/code-graph-freshness-guard.md:129:Expected: `.opencode/plugins` and `.opencode/skills` classify out-of-scope (excluded-dir), `README.md` classifies out-of-scope (non-source extension), a plain `src/foo.ts` stays in-scope; a fresh edit with no prior debounce state returns `defer-debounce`; a quiet-elapsed + warm-daemon edit returns `scan` with the exact `code-index.cjs code_graph_scan --warm-only` dispatch spec; `graphFreshness: "empty"` without the bootstrap opt-in returns `defer-empty`; the kill-switch returns `skip`/`disabled`.
.opencode/skills/system-code-graph/manual-testing-playbook/plugins-and-hooks/code-graph-freshness-guard.md:160:const result = spawnSync(process.execPath, [".opencode/skills/system-code-graph/runtime/hooks/claude/code-graph-freshness.cjs"], {
.opencode/skills/system-code-graph/manual-testing-playbook/plugins-and-hooks/code-graph-freshness-guard.md:164:console.log("exit status:", result.status);
