.opencode/skills/system-code-graph/manual-testing-playbook/mcp-tool-surface/code-graph-query-bm25-symbol-resolver.md:25:This scenario validates the BM25 symbol resolver on `code_graph_query`. When a subject cannot be resolved to a symbol by exact `symbol_id`, `fq_name` or `name` lookup, the default-off `SPECKIT_CODE_GRAPH_BM25_SYMBOL_RESOLVER` flag lets the handler attach ranked candidate symbols to the unresolved-subject error. The suggestions are marked `disambiguationOnly: true` and never run the structural query automatically. Exact resolution runs first and always wins, so an exact subject returns its real query result with no BM25 path taken. With the flag off an unresolved subject returns the plain error with no candidates.
.opencode/skills/system-code-graph/manual-testing-playbook/mcp-tool-surface/code-graph-query-bm25-symbol-resolver.md:35:- Expected signals: an exact subject resolves and returns its query result, a near-miss subject with the flag on returns an error envelope carrying `symbolResolution.resolver: "bm25"` and `disambiguationOnly: true` candidates, and the same near-miss subject with the flag off returns the plain error without candidates.
.opencode/skills/system-code-graph/manual-testing-playbook/mcp-tool-surface/code-graph-query-bm25-symbol-resolver.md:57:   Expected: the subject resolves and the query returns its structural result. `status` not `error`. No `symbolResolution` block.
.opencode/skills/system-code-graph/manual-testing-playbook/mcp-tool-surface/code-graph-query-bm25-symbol-resolver.md:77:4. **Exact resolution still wins with the flag on:** with `SPECKIT_CODE_GRAPH_BM25_SYMBOL_RESOLVER=true` still set, repeat the exact subject from step 1. Expected: the subject resolves by exact match and returns the structural result with no `symbolResolution` block, proving the resolver runs only after exact matching misses.
