.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/manual-testing-playbook/ux-hooks/result-provenance.md:2:title: "217 -- Result provenance (graph evidence)"
.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/manual-testing-playbook/ux-hooks/result-provenance.md:3:description: "Validates the graphEvidence envelope on Stage 2 fusion output, including contributing edge IDs, community IDs, and boost factors per result."
.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/manual-testing-playbook/ux-hooks/result-provenance.md:6:id: ux-hooks-result-provenance
.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/manual-testing-playbook/ux-hooks/result-provenance.md:11:# 217 -- Result provenance (graph evidence)
.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/manual-testing-playbook/ux-hooks/result-provenance.md:15:This scenario validates the per-result `graphEvidence` field that surfaces on Stage 2 fusion when graph signals contribute to ranking. It exercises the edge ID list, community ID list, boost factor breakdown, and the `SPECKIT_RESULT_PROVENANCE` kill-switch.
.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/manual-testing-playbook/ux-hooks/result-provenance.md:21:- Objective: Verify `graphEvidence` is attached to results that received graph-derived boosts and contains the contributing edge IDs, community IDs, and boost factors.
.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/manual-testing-playbook/ux-hooks/result-provenance.md:22:- Real user request: `Please validate graph evidence provenance on search results: prove graphEvidence is populated for graph-boosted results with edge IDs, communities, and boost factors, and that SPECKIT_RESULT_PROVENANCE=false strips the field.`
.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/manual-testing-playbook/ux-hooks/result-provenance.md:23:- Prompt: `Validate result provenance and confirm graphEvidence surfaces edge IDs, community IDs, and boost factors per result.`
.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/manual-testing-playbook/ux-hooks/result-provenance.md:25:- Expected signals: graph-boosted results carry a `graphEvidence` object; the object includes contributing causal edge IDs with relation types, community IDs, and individual boost factors; results without graph contribution do not carry `graphEvidence`; `SPECKIT_RESULT_PROVENANCE=false` strips the field.
.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/manual-testing-playbook/ux-hooks/result-provenance.md:27:- Pass/fail: PASS when `graphEvidence` surfaces for graph-boosted results, contains documented fields, and the kill-switch strips the field. FAIL when the field is missing for boosted results, content is incomplete, or the kill-switch has no effect.
.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/manual-testing-playbook/ux-hooks/result-provenance.md:36:Validate result provenance and confirm graphEvidence surfaces edge IDs, community IDs, and boost factors per result.
.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/manual-testing-playbook/ux-hooks/result-provenance.md:45:5. Assert the field contains: a list of contributing edge IDs (including the one created in step 2) with their relation types; a list of community IDs the result belongs to (or empty if not in any community); a breakdown of boost factors that contributed to the final score.
.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/manual-testing-playbook/ux-hooks/result-provenance.md:46:6. Locate a result that did not receive a graph boost. Assert its envelope does not carry `graphEvidence` (or carries an empty/null value).
.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/manual-testing-playbook/ux-hooks/result-provenance.md:47:7. Set `SPECKIT_RESULT_PROVENANCE=false` in MCP env, restart, repeat step 3. Assert the `graphEvidence` field is absent on all results.
.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/manual-testing-playbook/ux-hooks/result-provenance.md:53:- Boosted result carries `graphEvidence` with edge IDs, communities, and boost factors.
.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/manual-testing-playbook/ux-hooks/result-provenance.md:54:- Unboosted result has no `graphEvidence`.
.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/manual-testing-playbook/ux-hooks/result-provenance.md:55:- Flag-off run strips the field on all results.

