.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-opencode/changelog/v1.3.15.2.md:59:- **Per-tier `--variant` ranges are carried over, not re-measured.** The Pro-tier reasoning-effort restriction (`medium`/`high`/`xhigh`, vs the full `none`..`xhigh` for base/Fast) was a documented fact for `gpt-5.5-pro`; it is generalized here to all four GPT-5.6 Pro slugs (`gpt-5.6-pro` / `gpt-5.6-sol-pro` / `gpt-5.6-terra-pro` / `gpt-5.6-luna-pro`) as a documentation default. `opencode models openai` lists slugs but not variant ranges, and the source `gpt-5.5-pro` slug is no longer in the live catalog to re-check, so this generalization is inferred — smoke-test a Pro slug at `--variant low` before relying on the restriction. This caveat is now flagged **inline** in `references/cli-reference.md` §5 (the point of use SKILL.md directs readers to), matching the file's convention for its other unverified mappings.
